Author: Ruriko Yoshida
Date: July 6th, 2004
==================================================================
You need to have Linux system with gcc2.6 or higher....

In order to set up LattE:

1,) Create a directory for LattE, say "latte."

2,) Download the file for linux machine to the directory for LattE.

3,) To install LattE, type:

./install

=======================================
Then you can find the directory "LattE" in the corrent directory and go to 
the directory "LattE."  You can find all binaries you need.

If you have any questions please send us email at latte@math.ucdavis.edu 
or ruriko@math.duke.edu

Ruriko Yoshida


